<p>A construction crane collapsed onto a moving passenger train in northeastern Thailand on Wednesday, derailing several carriages and sparking a brief fire, authorities and media reported. Reports of fatalities rose through the day as rescue teams searched the wreckage, with several outlets citing at least 29 deaths and dozens of injuries. The crash happened along a rail corridor where an elevated high-speed rail line is under construction above the existing track, according to multiple reports.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/PFGzcxH2cFqz0US6yXOt-zAtqbbbbg4IaZAyCbx3COXZ84zzIQS3GO03-7TaPgQEj7o8j6hDQuk7dA85FxlLKTKK8M_xxPs7Fr3SBHnEn7GE' alt='Rescue workers beside the wreckage after a construction crane collapse derailed a train in Thailand’s Nakhon Ratchasima province.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Route and crowding: Officials said nearly 200 people were aboard the Bangkok-to-Ubon Ratchathani service when the crane struck and multiple cars derailed in Nakhon Ratchasima province.</li><li>Eyewitness account: A local resident told AFP he heard a loud sliding noise followed by two explosions and described the crane metal as slicing into the middle carriage.</li><li>Rescue pause: District police chief Thatchapon Chinnawong said rescuers temporarily paused operations due to a reported “chemical leakage” risk at the scene.</li><li>Project backdrop: Several outlets linked the worksite to a Beijing-backed high-speed rail project tied to the Belt and Road Initiative, with plans to connect Bangkok toward Kunming via Laos by 2028.</li><li>Fire and smoke: Verified and broadcast footage showed smoke rising from the wreckage and the train cars tilted or on their side, as emergency teams worked nearby.</li></ul><blockquote>At around 9:00am, I heard a loud noise, like something sliding down from above, followed by two explosions - Mitr Intrpanya</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Nakhon Ratchasima provincial public relations department: The department said a crane collapsed onto a train, causing it to derail and catch fire. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1966919/over-20-killed-dozens-injured-in-train-accident-at-china-backed-project-in-thailand'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>District police (Sikhio): Police described a crane strike that derailed multiple carriages and reported ongoing casualty assessment, including checks on how many injured were critical. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1966919/over-20-killed-dozens-injured-in-train-accident-at-china-backed-project-in-thailand'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>International media/official briefings: Early tolls varied across initial reports before converging higher as rescue and verification continued through the day. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/construction-crane-falls-passenger-train-northeastern-thailand-killing-129191335'>ABC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2026/01/14/g-s1-105943/construction-crane-falls-onto-moving-train-thailand'>A construction crane falls onto a moving train in Thailand, killing at least 29 people</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/construction-crane-falls-passenger-train-northeastern-thailand-killing-129191335'>A construction crane falls on a passenger train in northeastern Thailand, killing at least 12 people</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/jan/14/thailand-train-crane-accident-deaths'>At least 22 killed as crane collapses on train in Thailand</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/nakhon-ratchasima-22-killed-as-crane-collapse-derails-train-in-thailand-10746660#publisher=newsstand'>Crane At China-Backed Rail Project Collapses, Derails Thailand Train, 28 Dead</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/22-killed-as-crane-collapse-derails-passenger-train-in-thailand-13968569.html'>22 killed as crane collapse derails passenger train in Thailand</a> - firstpost.c